{"id":78772,"title":"[The application of essential oils for the treatment of acute rhinitis in the breastfed infants].","abstract":"Specific features of the clinical course of acute rhinitis in the breastfed infants are described in conjunction with the approaches to the treatment of this condition. Special attention is given to the possibilities of inhalation of essential oils for this purpose. The results of the estimation of the effectiveness and tolerability of these substances are discussed with special reference to the \"Dyshi\" composition designed for monotherapy of infectious rhinitis in the children during the first year of life. ","date":"2014-02-28","categories":"Otorhinolaryngologic Diseases","split":"test","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24577033","annotations":[{"name":"Therapy","weight":0.841915,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Therapy"},{"name":"Infant","weight":0.760949,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Infant"},{"name":"Breastfeeding","weight":0.758002,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Breastfeeding"},{"name":"Acute (medicine)","weight":0.677638,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Acute_(medicine)"},{"name":"Inhalation","weight":0.606559,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Inhalation"},{"name":"Infection","weight":0.528221,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Infection"},{"name":"Chemical substance","weight":0.372176,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chemical_substance"},{"name":"Essential oil","weight":0.23318,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Essential_oil"},{"name":"Clinical trial","weight":0.155524,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Clinical_trial"},{"name":"Oil","weight":0.117545,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Oil"},{"name":"Rhinitis","weight":0.0639325,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rhinitis"},{"name":"Estimation","weight":0.0391252,"wikipedia_article":"http:/